BY AKINWALE ABOLUWADE, IBADAN The Olubadan designate, Dr. Lekan Balogun, has assured the Central Council of Ibadan Indigenes that he would not betray the confidence reposed in him. The incoming Olubadan, on Friday, pledged his support to the frontline Ibadan socio-cultural group in forging a common front. Balogun spoke while playing host to the executives of the CCII led by its President-General, Prince Oluyemisi Adeaga, at his Alarere residence in Ibadan. The new Olubadan, who acknowledged the contributions of the CCII, praised their doggedness, patriotism and sacrifice for the good of Ibadanland. Earlier, the President-General of CCII said that the purpose of the visit was to formally congratulate the Olubadan designate on the ratification of his appointment by Governor Seyi Makinde 